# 🤖 ROS2 Robotics Project

## 📌 Overview
This repository contains my work and experiments with **ROS2**.  
The project covers basic to intermediate concepts such as **Turtlesim, RViz, TFs, URDF modeling, Gazebo plugins, and spawning robots in Gazebo**.  
The focus was on learning how to simulate, visualize, and control robots in a ROS2 environment.

---

## ✨ Topics Covered
- 🐢 **Turtlesim** – basics of ROS2 nodes, topics, and publishing commands.  
- 👓 **RViz** – visualization of robot models, frames, and sensor data.  
- 🔄 **TF Frames** – defining and broadcasting coordinate transforms.  
- 🦴 **URDF (Links & Joints)** – building robot models.  
- 🛠️ **Gazebo Plugins** – adding sensors and controllers to robots.  
- 🌍 **Gazebo Simulation** – launching robots in simulation environments.  
- 🚀 **Spawn Robot in Gazebo** – deploying URDF models into Gazebo.  

